				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not familiar with NESLib at all, but the basic idea is, in psuedocode, something like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Draw blank tile where snake's tail is (draw_tile(blank, tail_x, tail_y)<br />Run snake's move routine<br />Draw head tile where snake's head is (draw_tile(snake_head, head_x, head_y))</div><br /><br />That's only two writes to the table per frame. It should be adequately quick. You can store the snake's &quot;previous tail position' before moving the snake, to allow you to remove the game logic from your render code.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

